-- PRESS DIGEST - Bulgaria - Sept 18
-- 
-- Thu Sep 18, 2014 02:21AM EDT
-- None



SOFIA, Sept 18 (Reuters) - These are some of the main stories in Bulgarian newspapers on Thursday. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

-- The Bulgarian government extended 28 million levs (18.42 million US dollar) in non-interest loans to five municipalities whose funds are blocked in troubled Corporate Commercial Bank<6C9.BB>. Another five municipalities have filed requests for loans worth 10 million levs. (Capital Daily, Sega, Trud) -- The electricity costs can increase by 10 percent as of October 1 to cover the shortfalls in the energy sector, the energy regulator said. (Capital daily, Trud, Presa, Sega, Dua, 24 Chasa, Monitor, Standart) -- A Serbian court ruled that Tsvetan Vassilev, the main shareholder in Corporate Commercial Bank, needs to stay in Belgrade and show up at Serbian police unit every day until it rules on an extradition request by Bulgaria. Vassilev is charged with embezzlement from the bank. (Capital Daily, Presa, Trud )